UNIFORM OUTSIDE INCOME RULE ASKED 
President Bush's ethics commission agreed today there should be a uniform limit 
on the outside income earned by top government officials but called on Congress 
to set the limit and to let the President exempt some activities, such as 
scholarly writing. 
The eight-member panel completed its fifth and final working day still sharply 
divided over moonlighting by judges, members of Congress, top executive branch 
officials and the most senior aides in all three branches. 
